com.callumbirks

Class Tree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.callumbirks.Tree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The generic type T which determines the type of the mField variable.

    public class Tree<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Generic implementation of a tree. The tree has one field of generic type T, and another private variable which stores an ArrayList of its children, each element being of type Tree<T>.
    Author:
    callumbirks

      • addChild

        public void addChild(T destParentField,
                     Tree<T> newChild)
              throws java.rmi.NoSuchObjectException
        An overload of the above function. This function uses the searchNode function to locate a node with an mField variable equal to the destParentField parameter. It then adds the newChild parameter as a child on the located node. If a node with the given value cannot be found, searchNode returns null, and this function throws a NoSuchObjectException.
        Parameters:
        destParentField - The mField variable of the parent node you wish to add a child to.
        newChild - A Tree<T> representing the new child node.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.NoSuchObjectException

      • removeChild

        public Tree<T> removeChild(T searchValue)
        An overload of the above function. Rather than removing the child at a given index from the current node, it searches across the whole tree for a child node with an mField variable of the given value, and then removes it. Returns the removed node if it was found, otherwise returns null.
        Parameters:
        searchValue - The mField variable of the child node you are looking to remove.
        Returns:
        The removed node, of type Tree<T>. If the node searched for was not found, returns null.

      • searchNode

        public Tree<T> searchNode(T searchValue)
        Searches for a node with an mField variable equal to the searchValue parameter. The search is completed using recursion and is a depth-first pre-order traversal. If the search value is found, returns an object of type Tree<T>, which is just a pointer therefore can be used to directly modify the node. If a node does not exist with the given value, the function returns null.
        Parameters:
        searchValue - The value to search for in the tree
        Returns:
        If node exists with given value, return that node, otherwise return null.
